The paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of minimizing total weighted completion time is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The development of efficient approximation schemes involves the use of mathematical programming and optimization techniques, which are also relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of new methods and techniques, which could be related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG) or information theory (cs.IT).
